Uses Buster.JS tests case to test a simple calculator

Prereq to run the test:
Node.js and Buster.JS installed

 - To run the test in browser:

buster-01$ buster static
Starting server on http://localhost:8282/

Width a browser navigate to the link (you may rightclick and open link)
Look at the result

- To run the test in Node.js, start the test server:
~$ buster server
buster-server running on http://localhost:1111

Width a browser navigate to the link (you may rightclick and open link) and capture your browsers.
buster-01$ buster test
Firefox 15.0.1, Linux:                                                                                 
1 test case, 7 tests, 7 assertions, 0 failures, 0 errors, 0 timeouts
Finished in 0.076s

With dots reporter:
buster-01$ buster test --reporter dots
Firefox 15.0.1, Linux:   
			.......
1 test case, 7 tests, 7 assertions, 0 failures, 0 errors, 0 timeouts
Finished in 0.065s

With tap reporter:
buster-01$ buster test --reporter tap
ok 1 Firefox 15.0.1, Linux Calcualtor should add two numbers
ok 2 Firefox 15.0.1, Linux Calcualtor calculator should exist
ok 3 Firefox 15.0.1, Linux Calcualtor adds two numbers
ok 4 Firefox 15.0.1, Linux Calcualtor substracts two numbers
ok 5 Firefox 15.0.1, Linux Calcualtor multiplies two numbers
ok 6 Firefox 15.0.1, Linux Calcualtor divides two numbers
ok 7 Firefox 15.0.1, Linux Calcualtor throw exception for anything else than numbers
1..7









